How to start this.. meh like this i spose

So some people like to tinker with things? yes? Some people like to say, try renovate their houses, some people try to fix their plumbing. Some people try to fix cars, alot fail.

Today I managed to install a boost gauge in my car, no great feat right? Well, I think it is, all things considered my car is 3 years old, still under warranty and so far owes me $45000. And here I am pulling it apart, modifying it, and worst of all, doing it myself. I so far have managed to change the clutch, change teh suspension, intall my boost gauge, both the vacuum set up and 2moro I will wire in the lighting for it. Next up I have a electric oil tempratue gauge and oil pressure gauge to install, which has to run through the dash of the car, hmm fun getting in there, but watch me do it, and why? why dont I just pay the $100 to install it? Because I'm poor and I would rather learn it myself.

Next step is to by a flash tuning unit, which is a trick peice of gear that lets me tune the cars motor in every aspect, from when the knock sensor stops the motor working, to simple fuel air ratio's. Now to tune this I need a laptop, too easy, ebay is great for cheap crap. Why would I want to try tune my own car when I can pay some1 to pull their own hair out for hours trying to get that extra half a kw of power? Because I like to learn, and I would rather be able to toy with it myself. 

At the moment I'm a 2nd year apprentice panel beater, I am starting to get really good at what I'm doing, its great, yet next year I want to start an external uni degree in one of three things. Psychology (always been a passion) councelling (same sort of thing, still helping people) or a business degree. I know its going to be hard, but hell its something I would love on my resume when I go for any new jobs. I figure by the time I have finished my degree I will well and truely be a good panel beater and be able to leave my trade and go do a little work as a psychologist/councellor. After a few years of that and learning how it all works I would love to go do an adult apprentiship as a mechanic, how I love tinkering with the mechanical side of cars.

So thats the change in life I am becoming so very keen about undertaking.

Lets just see how I go

Cars will forever rock my socks, untill I lose interest

The things I miss most

- Staying up till 5 am with nothing to do the next day
- staying up till 5 am with tafe in 3 hours
- that feeling of paranoia I used to always have
- writing poems for hours on ends
- the feeling of deep empathy
- the feeling of deep apathy
- training in a martial art just to keep myself focused on something, even if it was for 9 hour stints
- waking up at 4 pm
- driving in a car with no roof
- having to walk everywhere (I'm going to find this one again as I cant drive anymore)
- chasing chicks around trying to get some
- that feeling of nervousness and discomfort around a new girlfriend
- listening to new music
- having political discussions with others that dont share my veiw
- using my hands to write and not work
- never watching television on the basis it is unproductive
- running at night
- running at anytime!
- going to the gym (start again tommorow, yay!)
- wondering about things far beyond my comprehension for hours, days and weeks on end, just to come to no conclusion
- reading books, full in detail non fiction books
- destroying the bones in my shins for the sake of having some fun with my brother.


This settled life, this working life, it suits my expencive car habits, but it denies me of what I love. Maybe work for a few more years, make my mark, learn my trade, then start study again. Give up work and go try my hand at uni once again. All the while driving my beloved car.. which by the way, now has 7 thousand dollars of modifications done, (all thats changed is the suspension, clutch and gear selection lever..) ahh this car is going to be the end of me I swear

Today I have no fucking idea, and it makes me angry, it makes me sad and it leaves me so very very very confused. I dont understand I dont understand I dont understand I dont understand I dont understand I dont understand I dont understand I dont understand I dont understand. I really dont understand, I try to solve this problem, head on, I try to solve it by thinking for hours, I try to solve it by letting it slide, yet in the end, its still not solved. I tell her how I feel, I tell her what i'm thinking, I tell her everything and still I find no answers. I ask and ask and i'm still left confused. Its left me feeling small and alone, its left me feeling insecure and recluse. Its left me feeling unwanted most of all.

So enough pestering and enough asking and enough telling, today I walked away, for the very first time. It will be resolved i'm sure, but in the meantime, let me go insane and let me feel small, alone and so very confused because I DONT UNDERSTAND

A poem to summarise



I'll drive around for hours
with no one in the car
i'll drive and drive and drive
with no one about
listening to my music of choice
that will destroy me
but i will drive
with a strange look on my face
seeing no one
talking to
no one
i will just drive
like it makes me forget
like it helps
but it makes it worse
so i will drive
cause days like these
i've got to follow the white rabbit
untill i crash
untill i hit the bottom
so let me drive
for hour after hour
chewing holes in my wallet
with my expencive addiction
let me drive, yeah it will be all ok
all fine
let me drive
let me crash

"Little" - Something Corporate

Climbing out of the sky a man who could fly and a painting anyone could play.
It's a comic book crush that taught you to trust.
Staring out of the stands at a rock n roll band
and a hero no one else could save, it was never much but it's all that you gave.

And I wonder if you wonder, or did your stars finally explode?
Did the thunder pull you underneath the haze?
I'm amazed, then I let go. 

Little minds let little pain burn big old dreams with little flames,
and you don't think I understand.
Little holes in parachutes won't leave you falling,
if they do, it's because you want to land. 

Climbing out of his chair to fix the T.V. glare is a man
but no one knows he's there.
It's a Dramamine dream that kept them alive but lost.
She's got her plastic friends and a brand new Benz and she laughs,
"Hell, sometimes life ain't fair"
It's a comic book crush that got them nowhere. 

These elevator doors are closing again you leave before I planned.
I taste you walking down the hall.
You left your perfume on the nightstand.

You are one of the few out there whose wings are
truly ANGELIC. Selfless, powerful, and
divine, you are one blessed with a certain
cosmic grace. You are unequalled in
peacefulness, love, and beauty. As a Being of
Light your wings are massive and a soft white
or silver. Countless feathers grace them and
radiate the light within you for all the world
to see. You are a defender, protector, and
caretaker. Comforter of the weak and forgiver
of the wrong, chances are you are taken
advantage of once in awhile, maybe quite often.
But your innocence and wisdom sees the good in
everyone and so this mistreatment does not make
you colder. Merciful to the extreme, you will
try to help misguided souls find themselves and
peace. However not all Angelics allow
themselves to be gotten the better of - the
Seraphim for example will be driven to fighting
for the sake of Justice and protection of those
less powerful. Congratulations - and don't ever
